$ sysdm.cpl: Advanced

The *System Protection* tab of `→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl` allows to change
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl/Advanced/Performance[Performance] settings (Visual effects, processor scheduling, memory usage and virtual memory)
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl/Advanced/User-Profiles[User profiles] (Settings related to the desktop)
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl/Advanced/Startup-and-Recovery[Startup and recovery]
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl/Advanced/Environment-Variables[Environment variables]
